-- Nigeria's Sterling Bank posts 24 pct rise in 2013 profit
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Wed Mar 26, 2014 09:20AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, March 26 (Reuters) - Nigeria's Sterling Bank <STERLNB.LG> said on Wednesday its 2013 full-year pretax profit rose 24 percent to 9.31 billion naira ($56.51 million) from 7.49 billion naira the previous year.     The bank said it would pay a dividend of 0.25 naira per share from its profit, up 25 percent from the 0.20 naira paid in 2012.

